    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit utilizes a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system and six individual throttle bodies to achieve a high volumetric efficiency and a sharp throttle response. The power is managed through a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution during corner exit. The chassis has undergone preventative subframe reinforcement, and the suspension retains its factory-spec geometry for precise turn-in. Recent service includes a valve adjustment and inspection of the rod bearings. This is a robust driver's car that delivers a visceral, analog experience with its 8,000 RPM redline and balanced weight distribution.",
